-- WestLB Seeking More Time for Sale of WestImmo Unit, Handelsblatt Reports
-- B y   O l i v e r   S u e s s
-- 2010-10-13T05:33:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/westlb-seeking-more-time-for-sale-of-westimmo-unit-handelsblatt-reports.html
WestLB AG  wants the German
government to help it get more time to sell its real-estate
financing unit, Westdeutsche ImmobilienBank AG,  Handelsblatt 
reported, citing unidentified people from the financial industry
and government.  WestLB Chief Executive Officer  Dietrich Voigtlaender  raised
the topic at a meeting with representatives of the finance
ministry yesterday, the newspaper said.  Dusseldorf-based WestLB has to sell WestImmo under
conditions imposed by the European Commission when it approved
state aid.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Oliver Suess in Munich at 
 osuess@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at   fconnelly@bloomberg.net 
Edward Evans at   eevans3@bloomberg.net  